description:
Issue highlights:

  • This issue we have an exclusive never-before-published interview with the one and only Mark Hamill!
  • We announce the winners of the first Star Wars Insider awards!
  • An amazing all-new tale from the dangerous days of the Old Republic by Alexander Freed.
  • Insider celebrates the saga's most dedicated fans!

Issue highlights:

  • George Lucas and Kathleen Kennedy reveal what's coming next for the Star Wars saga.
  • A previously unpublished interview with Harrison Ford from 1977.
  • All-new Star Wars fiction from Timothy Zahn.
  • A fresh look at Celebration VI from the eyes of three very special guests.

Issue highlights:

  • Celebrating 100 episodes of Star Wars: The Clone Wars!
  • George Lucas and Flash Gordon: the untold story!
  • Han and Chewie back in action!
  • Behind-the-scenes of Smuggler's Gambit!

Issue highlights:

  • Supervising Director Dave Filoni on Star Wars: The Clone Wars Season Five, Ahsoka, and more!
  • The man behind the Star Wars newspaper strips, Russ Manning!
  • Exclusive Return of the Jedi unseen photos!
  • Meet Michael Price, writer of LEGO Star Wars specials!

Issue highlights:

  • Exclusive behind-the-scenes pictures from Return of the Jedi!
  • Yoda's first day on set revealed!
  • Stuart Freeborn tribute
  • Exclusive Star Wars fiction set during the early days of the Jedi!

Pick up this issue's Star Wars Insider and you'll find two EXCLUSIVE Star Wars: Jedi Legacy trading cards from Topps! We've teamed up with Topps to offer two sets of exclusive cards, click here to complete your collection!

Issue highlights:

  • A special profile looking at the pivotal role played by Padmé!
  • John Dykstra on the early days of Industrial Light & Magic!
  • Celebration Europe preview!
  • All-new Star Wars fiction!
  • Amazing behind-the-scenes art and photos from Episode VI!

This issue, Star Wars Insider celebrates the 30th anniversary of Return of the Jedi. We meet Mark Hamill, visit Jabba's Palace and reveal some more amazing behind-the-scenes images! Plus, there's a very special new member of the Insider team, as Warwick Davis joins as a guest editor - prepare for an Ewok takeover!

Issue highlights:

  • Warwick Davis recalls his first day on set and remembers the Ewok movies - plus he gives us some expert tips on how to act in a Star Wars movie!
  • Anthony Daniels and cast recall their time on Tatooine!
  • James Khan, author of the official novelization of Return of the Jedi, tells us about adapting the movie!
  • All-new Star Wars fiction!

Look out! It's Leia. This issue, Star Wars Insider pays tribute to a Star Wars icon - Princess Leia. We also celebrate 10 years of Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic. We reflect on the best bits of Star Wars Celebration Europe II. Plus, we reveal more fantastic rare images from Episode VI.

Issue highlights:

  • All about Leia! An exclusive profile on the "First Lady" of Star Wars!
  • Return of the Jedi - more fantastic rare images from Episode VI revealed!!
  • Game changer - How Star Wars roleplaying games sculpted the universe!
  • Hondo returns! All-new Star Wars fiction!

After over 35 years of Topps’ Star Wars trading cards, get ready for their most innovative set of trading cards yet in this special issue of Star Wars Insider!

Issue highlights:

  • Topps' exclusive!
  • Is the Sith Lord a victim or villain?!
  • An exclusive discussion about the first Star Wars' sequel novel!
  • We have a discussion with the artists McCaig & Chiang!
  • Author L. Neil Smith on the classic trilogy of Lando novels!!
  • Brand-new tale featuring Princess Leia!

SAY WHAT?! Could Riverdale's most dedicated bachelor really be falling for a girl? That's right, folks -- just in time for Valentine's Day, Jughead Jones gets bitten by the love bug! Read up on over 150 pages of Jughead's love connections in this digital exclusive collection. Will our favorite human vacuum ever be the same?!

More Mundane began one late September morning with a tiny sketchbook and an impulse. Noah Van Sciver then proceeded to transform the struggles and victories of daily life into a series of quietly poignant revelations interspersed with comedy. More Mundane was printed by the author in an exclusive 100-copy run, and will not be printed again.

Featured inside: Noah grows a mustache and is teased mercilessly! Famed printmaker Jasmyn Barbosa!

PLUS: Several naps! Parties! Concerts! Anger! Fun! Fun! Fun!
name: The Diary of Noah Van Sciver

volume.name: The Captain and the Kids Special Issue
Complete Maus: A Survivor's Tale: 25th Anniversary Edition

description: Hold onto your "slay" bells! The mental mire that is David Hutchison's brain has disgorged yet another engagingly disturbing adventure of everyone's favorite maniacal moppets, Mischief and Mayhem! The girls' dreams come true when they learn the secret location of Santa's workshop! The fun then begins as the girls trek to bring their dear Santa a gift -- no matter what! Together we learn a jolly ol' secret about Saint Nick and get to see special guest appearances by a host of other holiday icons! Fun for the whole family! (We won't say which family.)
